{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":492,"text":"I'm gonna talk a little bit about open-source security,"},{"time":5342,"text":"because we've got to get better at security"},{"time":7366,"text":"in this 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9386,"text":"Let me start by saying, let's look back to the 20th century,"},{"time":14073,"text":"and kind of get a sense of how that style of security"},{"time":17742,"text":"worked for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19220,"text":"This is Verdun, a battlefield in France"},{"time":22512,"text":"just north of the NATO headquarters in Belgium."},{"time":25829,"text":"At Verdun, in 1916, over a 300-day period,"},{"time":32445,"text":"700,000 people were killed,"},{"time":35573,"text":"so about 2,000 a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37632,"text":"If you roll it forward -- 20th-century security --"},{"time":41960,"text":"into the Second World War,"},{"time":44863,"text":"you see the Battle of Stalingrad,"},{"time":47345,"text":"300 days, 2 million people killed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50913,"text":"We go into the Cold War, and we continue"},{"time":53699,"text":"to try and build walls."},{"time":56478,"text":"We go from the trench warfare of the First World War"},{"time":60530,"text":"to the Maginot Line of the Second World War,"},{"time":64109,"text":"and then we go into the Cold War,"},{"time":66538,"text":"the Iron Curtain, the Berlin Wall."},{"time":69476,"text":"Walls don't work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71703,"text":"My thesis for us today is, instead of building walls"},{"time":76035,"text":"to create security, we need to build bridges."},{"time":79691,"text":"This is a famous bridge in Europe."},{"time":82115,"text":"It's in Bosnia-Herzegovina."},{"time":84237,"text":"It's the bridge over the Drina River,"},{"time":86476,"text":"the subject of a novel by Ivo Andrić,"},{"time":89302,"text":"and it talks about how,"},{"time":91060,"text":"in that very troubled part of Europe and the Balkans,"},{"time":94926,"text":"over time there's been enormous building of walls."},{"time":99069,"text":"More recently, in the last decade, we begin to see"},{"time":102160,"text":"these communities start, hesitatingly,"},{"time":105850,"text":"to come together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107403,"text":"I would argue, again, open-source security"},{"time":111576,"text":"is about connecting the international,"},{"time":114412,"text":"the interagency, the private-public,"},{"time":118159,"text":"and lashing it together with strategic communication,"},{"time":121924,"text":"largely in social networks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124392,"text":"So let me talk a little bit about why we need to do that,"},{"time":128757,"text":"because our global commons is under attack"},{"time":132504,"text":"in a variety of ways,"},{"time":134487,"text":"and none of the sources of threat to the global commons"},{"time":138253,"text":"will be solved by building walls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141082,"text":"Now, I'm a sailor, obviously."},{"time":143388,"text":"This is a ship, a liner, clipping through the Indian Ocean."},{"time":147997,"text":"What's wrong with this picture?"},{"time":150618,"text":"It's got concertina wire along the sides of it."},{"time":154129,"text":"That's to prevent pirates from attacking it."},{"time":156885,"text":"Piracy is a very active threat today"},{"time":159992,"text":"around the world. This is in the Indian Ocean."},{"time":163321,"text":"Piracy is also very active in the Strait of Malacca."},{"time":167112,"text":"It's active in the Gulf of Guinea."},{"time":169188,"text":"We see it in the Caribbean."},{"time":170945,"text":"It's a $10-billion-a-year discontinuity"},{"time":173732,"text":"in the global transport system."},{"time":177298,"text":"Last year, at this time, there were 20 vessels,"},{"time":180753,"text":"500 mariners held hostage."},{"time":183340,"text":"This is an attack on the global commons."},{"time":186963,"text":"We need to think about how to address it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189749,"text":"Let's shift to a different kind of sea,"},{"time":192199,"text":"the cyber sea."},{"time":194577,"text":"Here are photographs of two young men."},{"time":197814,"text":"At the moment, they're incarcerated."},{"time":200211,"text":"They conducted a credit card fraud that netted them"},{"time":205690,"text":"over 10 billion dollars."},{"time":209010,"text":"This is part of cybercrime which is a $2-trillion-a-year"},{"time":214036,"text":"discontinuity in the global economy."},{"time":217062,"text":"Two trillion a year."},{"time":218408,"text":"That's just under the GDP of Great Britain."},{"time":221870,"text":"So this cyber sea, which we know endlessly"},{"time":224797,"text":"is the fundamental piece of radical openness,"},{"time":228793,"text":"is very much under threat as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233323,"text":"Another thing I worry about in the global commons"},{"time":236346,"text":"is the threat posed by trafficking,"},{"time":239106,"text":"by the movement of narcotics, opium,"},{"time":243640,"text":"here coming out of Afghanistan through Europe"},{"time":247004,"text":"over to the United States."},{"time":248414,"text":"We worry about cocaine"},{"time":250571,"text":"coming from the Andean Ridge north."},{"time":252956,"text":"We worry about the movement of illegal weapons"},{"time":256174,"text":"and trafficking. Above all, perhaps,"},{"time":258593,"text":"we worry about human trafficking, and the awful cost of it."},{"time":262564,"text":"Trafficking moves largely at sea"},{"time":265219,"text":"but in other parts of the global commons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267706,"text":"This is a photograph, and I wish I could tell you"},{"time":272319,"text":"that this is a very high-tech piece of US Navy gear"},{"time":277191,"text":"that we're using to stop the trafficking."},{"time":279880,"text":"The bad news is,"},{"time":281680,"text":"this is a semi-submersible run by drug cartels."},{"time":287305,"text":"It was built in the jungles of South America."},{"time":291478,"text":"We caught it with that low-tech raft — (Laughter) —"},{"time":296340,"text":"and it was carrying six tons of cocaine."},{"time":300222,"text":"Crew of four. Sophisticated communications sweep."},{"time":304693,"text":"This kind of trafficking, in narcotics, in humans, in weapons,"},{"time":309755,"text":"God forbid, in weapons of mass destruction,"},{"time":312660,"text":"is part of the threat to the global commons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315549,"text":"And let's pull it together in Afghanistan today."},{"time":319703,"text":"This is a field of poppies in Afghanistan."},{"time":322449,"text":"Eighty to 90 percent of the world's poppy,"},{"time":325757,"text":"opium and heroin, comes out of Afghanistan."},{"time":329076,"text":"We also see there, of course, terrorism."},{"time":331855,"text":"This is where al Qaeda is staged from."},{"time":334157,"text":"We also see a very strong insurgency embedded there."},{"time":338763,"text":"So this terrorism concern is also part"},{"time":342543,"text":"of the global commons, and what we must address."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346616,"text":"So here we are, 21st century."},{"time":349929,"text":"We know our 20th-century tools are not going to work."},{"time":353648,"text":"What should we do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356213,"text":"I would argue that we will not deliver security"},{"time":360978,"text":"solely from the barrel of a gun."},{"time":363431,"text":"We will not deliver security solely from the barrel of a gun."},{"time":367594,"text":"We will need the application of military force."},{"time":370497,"text":"When we do it, we must do it well, and competently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373591,"text":"But my thesis is, open-source security is about international,"},{"time":379756,"text":"interagency, private-public connection pulled together"},{"time":384291,"text":"by this idea of strategic communication on the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390580,"text":"Let me give you a couple of examples of how this works in a positive way."},{"time":394141,"text":"This is Afghanistan. These are Afghan soldiers."},{"time":398612,"text":"They are all holding books."},{"time":400930,"text":"You should say, \"That's odd. I thought I read that"},{"time":405734,"text":"this demographic, young men and women"},{"time":409230,"text":"in their 20s and 30s, is largely illiterate in Afghanistan.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":414199,"text":"You would be correct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415940,"text":"Eighty-five percent cannot read"},{"time":418137,"text":"when they enter the security forces of Afghanistan."},{"time":421197,"text":"Why? Because the Taliban withheld education"},{"time":424344,"text":"during the period of time in which these men and women"},{"time":427628,"text":"would have learned to read."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429019,"text":"So the question is, so,"},{"time":430762,"text":"why are they all standing there holding books?"},{"time":434103,"text":"The answer is, we are teaching them to read"},{"time":437796,"text":"in literacy courses by NATO"},{"time":441164,"text":"in partnership with private sector entities,"},{"time":444659,"text":"in partnership with development agencies."},{"time":448046,"text":"We've taught well over 200,000 Afghan Security Forces"},{"time":452507,"text":"to read and write at a basic level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455055,"text":"When you can read and write in Afghanistan,"},{"time":457838,"text":"you will typically put a pen in your pocket."},{"time":460977,"text":"At the ceremonies, when these young men and women"},{"time":463565,"text":"graduate, they take that pen with great pride,"},{"time":467109,"text":"and put it in their pocket."},{"time":469209,"text":"This is bringing together international"},{"time":472151,"text":"— there are 50 nations involved in this mission —"},{"time":474997,"text":"interagency — these development agencies —"},{"time":477843,"text":"and private-public, to take on this kind of security."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481933,"text":"Now, we are also teaching them combat skills, of course,"},{"time":485567,"text":"but I would argue, open-source security"},{"time":488335,"text":"means connecting in ways that create"},{"time":491019,"text":"longer lasting security effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493871,"text":"Here's another example."},{"time":496171,"text":"This is a US Navy warship."},{"time":499610,"text":"It's called the Comfort."},{"time":501529,"text":"There's a sister ship called the Mercy."},{"time":504266,"text":"They are hospital ships."},{"time":506401,"text":"This one, the Comfort, operates throughout"},{"time":508483,"text":"the Caribbean and the coast of South America"},{"time":512094,"text":"conducting patient treatments."},{"time":514082,"text":"On a typical cruise, they'll do 400,000 patient treatments."},{"time":518823,"text":"It is crewed not strictly by military"},{"time":522614,"text":"but by a combination of humanitarian organizations:"},{"time":526518,"text":"Operation Hope, Project Smile."},{"time":529786,"text":"Other organizations send volunteers."},{"time":533372,"text":"Interagency physicians come out."},{"time":535627,"text":"They're all part of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537756,"text":"To give you one example of the impact this can have,"},{"time":540661,"text":"this little boy, eight years old,"},{"time":543890,"text":"walked with his mother two days"},{"time":547109,"text":"to come to the eye clinic put on by the Comfort."},{"time":550201,"text":"When he was fitted, over his extremely myopic eyes,"},{"time":555569,"text":"he suddenly looked up and said,"},{"time":558715,"text":"\"Mama, veo el mundo.\""},{"time":561953,"text":"\"Mom, I see the world.\""},{"time":564841,"text":"Multiply this by 400,000 patient treatments,"},{"time":568299,"text":"this private-public collaboration with security forces,"},{"time":572968,"text":"and you begin to see the power"},{"time":575037,"text":"of creating security in a very different way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578833,"text":"Here you see baseball players."},{"time":583130,"text":"Can you pick out the two US Army soldiers"},{"time":586950,"text":"in this photograph?"},{"time":588907,"text":"They are the two young men on either side"},{"time":591102,"text":"of these young boys. This is part of a series"},{"time":594117,"text":"of baseball clinics, where we have explored collaboration"},{"time":597960,"text":"between Major League Baseball,"},{"time":600068,"text":"the Department of State,"},{"time":601424,"text":"who sets up the diplomatic piece of this,"},{"time":603815,"text":"military baseball players, who are real soldiers"},{"time":608040,"text":"with real skills but participate in this mission,"},{"time":612073,"text":"and they put on clinics"},{"time":613975,"text":"throughout Latin America and the Caribbean,"},{"time":616061,"text":"in Honduras, in Nicaragua,"},{"time":619421,"text":"in all of the Central American and Caribbean nations"},{"time":624123,"text":"where baseball is so popular,"},{"time":625913,"text":"and it creates security."},{"time":628169,"text":"It shows role models to young men and women"},{"time":630627,"text":"about fitness and about life that I would argue"},{"time":634227,"text":"help create security for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638392,"text":"Another aspect of this partnership"},{"time":640989,"text":"is in disaster relief."},{"time":642940,"text":"This is a US Air Force helicopter participating"},{"time":646687,"text":"after the tsunami in 2004 which killed 250,000 people."},{"time":653641,"text":"In each of these major disasters — the tsunami in 2004,"},{"time":658152,"text":"250,000 dead, the Kashmiri earthquake in Pakistan, 2005,"},{"time":665026,"text":"85,000 dead,"},{"time":667052,"text":"the Haitian earthquake, about 300,000 dead,"},{"time":671721,"text":"more recently the awful earthquake-tsunami combination"},{"time":676612,"text":"which struck Japan and its nuclear industry —"},{"time":679976,"text":"in all of these instances, we see partnerships"},{"time":683063,"text":"between international actors,"},{"time":686385,"text":"interagency, private-public working with security forces"},{"time":690293,"text":"to respond to this kind of natural disaster."},{"time":694119,"text":"So these are examples of this idea of open-source security."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698471,"text":"We tie it together, increasingly, by doing things like this."},{"time":703142,"text":"Now, you're looking at this thinking, \"Ah, Admiral,"},{"time":706053,"text":"these must be sea lanes of communication,"},{"time":709239,"text":"or these might be fiber optic cables.\""},{"time":712039,"text":"No. This is a graphic of the world according to Twitter."},{"time":717231,"text":"Purple are tweets. Green are geolocation."},{"time":723799,"text":"White is the synthesis."},{"time":725845,"text":"It's a perfect evocation of that great population survey,"},{"time":729930,"text":"the six largest nations in the world in descending order:"},{"time":733677,"text":"China, India, Facebook, the United States,"},{"time":736355,"text":"Twitter and Indonesia. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":740677,"text":"Why do we want to get in these nets?"},{"time":742440,"text":"Why do we want to be involved?"},{"time":744250,"text":"We talked earlier about the Arab Spring,"},{"time":746106,"text":"and the power of all this."},{"time":747507,"text":"I'll give you another example,"},{"time":748850,"text":"and it's how you move this message."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751103,"text":"I gave a talk like this in London a while back"},{"time":753436,"text":"about this point. I said, as I say to all of you,"},{"time":756824,"text":"I'm on Facebook. Friend me."},{"time":758970,"text":"Got a little laugh from the audience."},{"time":761097,"text":"There was an article which was run by AP, on the wire."},{"time":766328,"text":"Got picked up in two places in the world:"},{"time":768844,"text":"Finland and Indonesia."},{"time":771192,"text":"The headline was: NATO Admiral Needs Friends."},{"time":775082,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":776565,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":779109,"text":"Which I do. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":781663,"text":"And the story was a catalyst,"},{"time":784220,"text":"and the next morning I had hundreds"},{"time":786939,"text":"of Facebook friend requests"},{"time":788574,"text":"from Indonesians and Finns,"},{"time":791091,"text":"mostly saying, \"Admiral, we heard you need a friend,"},{"time":794073,"text":"and oh, by the way, what is NATO?\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":797675,"text":"So ... (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":799727,"text":"Yeah, we laugh, but this is how we move the message,"},{"time":803813,"text":"and moving that message is how we connect"},{"time":806548,"text":"international, interagency, private-public,"},{"time":808999,"text":"and these social nets to help create security."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812869,"text":"Now, let me hit a somber note."},{"time":816302,"text":"This is a photograph of a brave British soldier."},{"time":820060,"text":"He's in the Scots Guards."},{"time":822266,"text":"He's standing the watch in Helmand,"},{"time":824012,"text":"in southern Afghanistan."},{"time":826276,"text":"I put him here to remind us,"},{"time":828932,"text":"I would not want anyone to leave the room thinking"},{"time":832259,"text":"that we do not need capable, competent militaries"},{"time":836472,"text":"who can create real military effect."},{"time":839707,"text":"That is the core of who we are and what we do,"},{"time":842802,"text":"and we do it to protect freedom, freedom of speech,"},{"time":846858,"text":"all the things we treasure in our societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849823,"text":"But, you know, life is not an on-and-off switch."},{"time":854082,"text":"You don't have to have a military that is either"},{"time":856471,"text":"in hard combat or is in the barracks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860274,"text":"I would argue life is a rheostat."},{"time":865057,"text":"You have to dial it in,"},{"time":867586,"text":"and as I think about how we create security"},{"time":870855,"text":"in this 21st century, there will be times"},{"time":873507,"text":"when we will apply hard power in true war and crisis,"},{"time":878636,"text":"but there will be many instances,"},{"time":880557,"text":"as we've talked about today,"},{"time":882315,"text":"where our militaries can be part of creating"},{"time":885507,"text":"21st-century security, international,"},{"time":889561,"text":"interagency, private-public,"},{"time":891969,"text":"connected with competent communication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896525,"text":"I would close by saying that we heard earlier today"},{"time":901012,"text":"about Wikipedia. I use Wikipedia all the time"},{"time":904975,"text":"to look up facts, and as all of you appreciate,"},{"time":908136,"text":"Wikipedia is not created by 12 brilliant people"},{"time":912289,"text":"locked in a room writing articles."},{"time":914764,"text":"Wikipedia, every day, is tens of thousands of people"},{"time":918477,"text":"inputting information, and every day millions of people"},{"time":923277,"text":"withdrawing that information."},{"time":925140,"text":"It's a perfect image for the fundamental point"},{"time":928760,"text":"that no one of us is as smart as all of us thinking together."},{"time":933382,"text":"No one person, no one alliance, no one nation,"},{"time":937042,"text":"no one of us is as smart as all of us thinking together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941823,"text":"The vision statement of Wikipedia is very simple:"},{"time":946505,"text":"a world in which every human being can freely share"},{"time":949619,"text":"in the sum of all knowledge."},{"time":951252,"text":"My thesis for you is that by combining international,"},{"time":955730,"text":"interagency, private-public, strategic communication,"},{"time":959900,"text":"together, in this 21st century,"},{"time":963365,"text":"we can create the sum of all security."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966632,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":969089,"text":"Thank you very much. Thank you. Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}